Gangaur is a vibrant, 18-day festival primarily celebrated in Rajasthan, India, honoring the union of Lord Shiva (Gan) and Goddess Parvati (Gauri) and symbolizing marital bliss, spring, and harvest. 
The name “Gangaur” is derived from “Gan” (Shiva) and “Gauri” (Parvati), signifying the worship of both deities.

A big thank you to @rjshruti & @superneeil for bringing me to this place “ HIDDEN “ ! This hidden gem was everything I had been waiting from a very long time to go with my favourite people. 

Soooo lemme share my experience : ahem ahem !! We sat around a cozy bonfire, roasting marshmallows to perfection, sipping on rich hot chocolate, and simply soaking in the beauty of the night. The chilly air made everything feel even more special, wrapping us in a warmth that had nothing to do with the fire but everything to do with the moment.
This adventure was pure magic, and I’ll always cherish it di !!!
